mystman12 2023-02-23 8:41 PM
I'm hesitant to put all this out here because I don't want to send people on a wild goose chase (As often happened during the ARG), but... I wish we could figure out just a few more of the locations used in the ACP video. Someone brought up the idea that maybe the first letter of the city each shot is filmed in can be taken and, when placed in the order of the shots, spell out a message. I took some time to compile some info based on that and @Flur's post, and unfortunately there isn't enough info to know if that theory is right or not. There are 26 shots, not including the intro and outro logo shots, so the message would presumably have 26 letters. I've assigned each shot a number based on when it first appears. Each number/location represents a unique letter. 1 is H for Hamburg, 5 is M for Montague, and 20 is O for Owatonna. We don't know any of the others yet. There is a total of 13 different locations/letters (There are 14 unique shots, but one of them is the same location as another). I've also counted the frequency of each location/letter. If we could figure out a couple more locations I think we could figure out pretty quickly if this is a dead-end or not, but I've tried searching for a few and there's barely anything to go off of. Locations like 3 are just a couple of houses and rolling hills, you can't find that without getting really lucky. I also tried searching for the train shots by following some railways, but I then learned that there are a lot more railways in the States than I thought haha.

mystman12
I'm hesitant to put all this out here because I don't want to send people on a wild goose chase (As often happened during the ARG), but... I wish we could figure out just a few more of the locations used in the ACP video. Someone brought up the idea that maybe the first letter of the city each shot is filmed in can be taken and, when placed in the order of the shots, spell out a message. I took some time to compile some info based on that and @Flur's post, and unfortunately there isn't enough info to know if that theory is right or not. There are 26 shots, not including the intro and outro logo shots, so the message would presumably have 26 letters. I've assigned each shot a number based on when it first appears. Each number/location represents a unique letter. 1 is H for Hamburg, 5 is M for Montague, and 20 is O for Owatonna. We don't know any of the others yet. There is a total of 13 different locations/letters (There are 14 unique shots, but one of them is the same location as another). I've also counted the frequency of each location/letter. If we could figure out a couple more locations I think we could figure out pretty quickly if this is a dead-end or not, but I've tried searching for a few and there's barely anything to go off of. Locations like 3 are just a couple of houses and rolling hills, you can't find that without getting really lucky. I also tried searching for the train shots by following some railways, but I then learned that there are a lot more railways in the States than I thought haha.
